"{\"uid\": \"theblaze.com-news-russell-brand-explores-what-was-revealed-by-the-olympics-symbolic-attack-on-christianity\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Brand intimated there is an effort underway to steer people away from the divine and toward an Epicurean prison for the spirit.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 95, \"end\": 104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Epicureanism\", \"score\": 0.9999999972828846, \"rank\": 2.717137667530847e-09, \"text\": \"Epicurean\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Epicureanism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Epicureanism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before cobbling together the first of several failed republics, French revolutionaries slaughtered Christian clerics, looted churches, banned Catholicism, and embarked on a campaign to altogetherde-Christianizethe country.\", \"from\": 129, \"to\": 351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 193, \"end\": 215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French revolutionaries\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\"}, {\"begin\": 228, \"end\": 237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.99999999870397, \"rank\": 1.29598617823622e-09, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some revolutionaries went so far as to attempt to replace the longstanding statereligionwith the atheistic Cult of Reason.\", \"from\": 353, \"to\": 475, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To this end, cultists swapped out the remaining religious statues in Notre Dame Cathedral for secular busts, engaged in rituals mocking those once practiced on the altar, and paraded around hyper-sexualized women, including an actress meant to portray the goddess of reason.\", \"from\": 476, \"to\": 750, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a similar spirit, the French kicked off the 2024 Olympics with anti-Christian mockery and substitution - although this time, they opted for men pretending to be hyper-sexualized women.\", \"from\": 752, \"to\": 939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 777, \"end\": 783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9714509771458368, \"rank\": 0.02705894488944883, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 818, \"end\": 832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antichrist\", \"score\": 0.8860311602361676, \"rank\": 0.1282881288692623, \"text\": \"anti-Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antichrist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antichrist\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony's designer, Thomas Jolly,staged a scenefor broadcast clearly intended to resemble Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper.\\\"\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 1074, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 966, \"end\": 972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.999999999958618, \"rank\": 3.817043985992341e-11, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}, {\"begin\": 1036, \"end\": 1053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.917067744722569e-29, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, instead of faithfully depicting Christ and his apostles, Jolly had a cast of transvestites strike iconic poses on either side of a morbidly obese individual wearing a crown-like halo.\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1215, \"end\": 1229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Obesity\", \"score\": 0.9998740637605118, \"rank\": 0.00012595210141208064, \"text\": \"morbidly obese\", \"types\": [\"Q12136\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Obesity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Obesity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'They attempt, in fact, to obdurate the very principle of the divine.'\", \"from\": 1271, \"to\": 1341, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Later, a virtually naked man painted blue - who was apparently supposed to be Dionysus, the Greek god of wine-making and ritual madness - who was set upon the table on a plate in front of the mock apostolate proceeded to sing.\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1569, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1421, \"end\": 1429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1121555288401416e-27, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 1435, \"end\": 1440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9282159878374535, \"rank\": 0.07490955325488671, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a recent op-ed for Blaze News, Sen. Mike Lee (R-Utah)noted:  Newly baptized actor and podcast host Russell Brandrecentlyponderedprecisely what symbols these would-be conquerors are attempting to advance as well as what is ultimately at the heart of the French's latest cultish display.\", \"from\": 1573, \"to\": 1861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1612, \"end\": 1620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Lee_(New_Zealand_politician)\", \"score\": 0.4973884692646734, \"rank\": 0.6197916666666509, \"text\": \"Mike Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Lee_(New_Zealand_politician)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Lee_(New_Zealand_politician)\"}, {\"begin\": 1675, \"end\": 1682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bertrand_Russell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.924818970087935e-28, \"text\": \"Russell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bertrand_Russell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bertrand_Russell\"}, {\"begin\": 1829, \"end\": 1835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9714509771458368, \"rank\": 0.02705894488944883, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wonder when it became explicit that what we are engaged in is a type ofspiritual warfare; that secularism, rationalism, and materialism themselves are kind of godless, not even pantheistic or pagan faiths,\\\" said Brand.\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 2084, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They attempt, in fact, to obdurate the very principle of the divine.\\\"\", \"from\": 2085, \"to\": 2155, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brand noted further that he was struck by the \\\"deliberate evocation of Christian imagery in order to what?\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2228, \"end\": 2237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.99999999870397, \"rank\": 1.29598617823622e-09, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Deride it?\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2274, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In order to what?\", \"from\": 2275, \"to\": 2292, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Attack it?\", \"from\": 2293, \"to\": 2303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Undermine it?\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2317, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What are the values that are being proposed here?\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2367, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Is it hedonism?\", \"from\": 2368, \"to\": 2383, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Is it decadence?\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Is it individualism?\", \"from\": 2401, \"to\": 2421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Is it that the self - your own personal set of decrees, desires and edicts are the apex and supreme hierarchy of ideologies?\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2546, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That there is nothing superior and supreme to which we have to surrender?\\\"\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brand concluded that what is behind this propaganda is in line with the project of the Paris' 18th century cultists of reason: to \\\"derail the sacred and engender a kind of state of nihilism where everything might be regarded as a truth.\\\"\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2710, \"end\": 2715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999990391188, \"rank\": 9.607186553125734e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the podcast host later indicated he was not altogether convinced that the coloration of the Dionysus character in a corpse-like color and his presentation as a meal was intended to be a direct mockery of the Eucharist, he said the display was at the very least oriented toward \\\"nihilism, unbelief, celebration of selfishness.\\\"\", \"from\": 2862, \"to\": 3194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2960, \"end\": 2968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1121555288401416e-27, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 3076, \"end\": 3085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"score\": 0.9196200130616118, \"rank\": 0.08740560655814016, \"text\": \"Eucharist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the basis of Brand's comments in a video posted Wednesday to his X account, it appears he regards this nihilistic project as a trap for the soul.\", \"from\": 3196, \"to\": 3344, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There are times when I have told you that I felt far for Christ,\\\"saidBrand.\", \"from\": 3346, \"to\": 3422, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is a verse that brought me back into connection with our Lord.\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3491, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's from Isaiah.\", \"from\": 3492, \"to\": 3509, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3502, \"end\": 3508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isaiah\", \"score\": 0.9999933881286176, \"rank\": 6.611915191795898e-06, \"text\": \"Isaiah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isaiah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isaiah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Fear not, for I have redeemed you.\", \"from\": 3510, \"to\": 3545, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have called you by your name.\", \"from\": 3546, \"to\": 3577, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are mine.'\\\"\", \"from\": 3578, \"to\": 3593, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My feelings of faith have altered lately because I have had the sense that through fear I might take back my self will, that I might, through fear, think I have to be in control of the situation,\\\" continued Brand.\", \"from\": 3595, \"to\": 3809, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If you feel that you are being attacked, if you are under threat, it seems obvious, rational, sensible, to take back control.\\\"\", \"from\": 3810, \"to\": 3937, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But the sensation of faith - allowing Christ in His sub-molecular potency, right down to the granule, right out into the cosmological, to order all things, for we are dealing with the king of eternity,\\\" added Brand.\", \"from\": 3939, \"to\": 4155, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brand noted that surrender to Christ means liberation from \\\"the cubic reality afforded to you by materialism and rationalism, and into a transcendent realm where you are given grace - where once I have accepted sin and surrendered, and allowed Him to carry me, I am granted a new freedom.\", \"from\": 4157, \"to\": 4445, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"...\", \"from\": 4446, \"to\": 4449, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not belong to myself anymore and that is true freedom.\\\"\", \"from\": 4450, \"to\": 4510, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Like Blaze News?\", \"from\": 4512, \"to\": 4528, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bypass the censors, sign up for our newsletters, and get stories like this direct to your inbox.Sign up here!\", \"from\": 4529, \"to\": 4638, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Joseph MacKinnon\", \"from\": 4640, \"to\": 4656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4640, \"end\": 4646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\", \"score\": 0.9999999226138273, \"rank\": 7.738633957543268e-08, \"text\": \"Joseph\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\"}]}]}"